I have reviewed the existing `ProductList.tsx` and `globals.css` to add the necessary CSS for displaying a list of products effectively. Below, I will add some CSS styles specifically tailored for the product list to ensure it looks appealing and is user-friendly.

### Updated CSS for Product List

I will enhance the CSS to style the product list in the `globals.css` file.

```css
.product-list {
  padding: 20px;
  max-width: 800px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

.product-list h2 {
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
  font-size: 2rem;
  color: var(--foreground);
}

.products {
  display: grid;
  gap: 20px;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
}

.product {
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  padding: 15px;
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  background-color: var(--card);
  transition: transform 0.2s ease-in-out;
}

.product:hover {
  transform: translateY(-5px);
}

.product h3 {
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  margin: 10px 0;
  color: var(--primary);
}

.product p {
  color: var(--secondary-foreground);
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}

.product p:last-child {
  font-weight: bold;
  color: var(--destructive);
}
```

### Explanation of Changes

- **Layout**: The `.products` class now uses a grid layout to organize product items in responsive columns.
- **Styling**: Added hover effects, border, padding, and background color for the `.product` class to make each item stand out.
- **Typography**: Enhanced font sizes and colors for better readability and aesthetics.

I will now update the `globals.css` file with these new styles.
